    • Method Detail

      • setStorageFactory

        @CanIgnoreReturnValue
public EventBus.Builder setStorageFactory(StorageFactory storageFactory)
        Specifies an StorageFactory to configure this EventBus.

        This StorageFactory instance will be used to create an instance of EventStore for this EventBus, if EventStore was not explicitly set in the builder.

        Either a StorageFactory or an EventStore are mandatory to create an EventBus.

        See Also:
        EventBus.Builder.setEventStore(EventStore)

      • getStorageFactory

        public java.util.Optional<StorageFactory> getStorageFactory()

      • setEventStore

        @CanIgnoreReturnValue
public EventBus.Builder setEventStore(EventStore eventStore)
        Specifies EventStore to be used when creating new EventBus.

        This method can be called if neither EventBus.Builder.setEventStoreStreamExecutor(Executor) nor EventBus.Builder.setStorageFactory(StorageFactory) were called before.

        Either a StorageFactory or an EventStore must be set to create an EventBus.

        See Also:
        EventBus.Builder.setEventStoreStreamExecutor(Executor), EventBus.Builder.setStorageFactory(StorageFactory)

      • getEventStore

        public java.util.Optional<EventStore> getEventStore()

      • setEventStoreStreamExecutor

        @CanIgnoreReturnValue
public EventBus.Builder setEventStoreStreamExecutor(java.util.concurrent.Executor eventStoreStreamExecutor)
        Specifies an Executor for returning event stream from EventStore.

        This Executor instance will be used for creating new EventStore instance when building EventBus, if EventStore was not explicitly set in the builder.

        If an Executor is not set in the builder, MoreExecutors.directExecutor() will be used.

        See Also:
        EventBus.Builder.setEventStore(EventStore)

      • getEventStoreStreamExecutor

        public java.util.Optional<java.util.concurrent.Executor> getEventStoreStreamExecutor()

      • setEnricher

        public EventBus.Builder setEnricher(EventEnricher enricher)
        Sets a custom Enricher for events posted to the EventBus which is being built.

        If the Enricher is not set, the enrichments will NOT be supported for the EventBus instance built.

        Parameters:
        enricher - the Enricher for events or null if enrichment is not supported

        If not set directly, Level.TRACE will be used.
